definitions.definition: The tallest mast of a sailing ship that has more than one mast; particularly a full-rigged ship.
The second-foremost mast of a non-sailing ship with more than one mast.

main_definition: ( nautical ) The tallest mast of a sailing ship that has more than one mast; particularly a full-rigged ship.
secondary_definitions: ( nautical ) The second-foremost mast of a non-sailing ship with more than one mast.
